    "Published Weekly by The Chicago World Pub Co Inc EAST 35TH STREET CHICAGO 16 ILLINOIS VICTORY 58S5 JACOB R TIPPER Founder and Publisher18761943 f RRY K TIPPER Editor and Publisher YYAN V TIPPER General Manager WARD L LANECity Editor SUBSCRIPTION RATES fIREE MONTHS m 2 c ix months NE YEAR 400 Entered as Second Class Matter at the Post Officeat Chicago lllinoisu nder the Act of March 8 1879 ADVERTISING RATES FURNISHED UPON REQUEST Spend your money in your own community Dont spend your money where you cant work Teach your dollars to have more sense Cut down southern representation in Congress Use your buying power as you use your ballot SATURDAY JUrE 5 1948 Forecasting The Price Trend Will commodity prices go up Go down Stay where they are Newsweek recently asked 50 leading economists connected with business labor governmental statistical and educational in fctitutions to rorecast the price trend for the balance of the year Twentysix thought prices would continue upward 14 said they will remain about the same and the remaining ten believe they will lie lower by the years end Averaging the answers the concensus is that prices wont mange substantially one way or the other"
